 $\\sim3.5$ kpc and an apocenter of $\\sim17$\nkpc. The phase-space structure and stellar population of the stream show that\nits progenitor must have been a globular cluster that was disrupted only\n$\\sim240$ Myr ago. We do not detect any significant overdensity of stars along\nthe stream that would indicate the presence of a progenitor, and conclude that\nthe stream is all that is left of the progenitor.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 3 Jan 2015 17:24:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 28 Jul 2015 15:35:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-08-19"}
